  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) Class I-III.

          -  Patient is undergoing elective hand or forearm surgery.

          -  Patient is an adult, 18 years old or older.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Morbid obesity (calculated body mass index &gt; 35 kg/m2).

          -  Patient unable to cooperate.

          -  Patient with a known brachial plexus injury.

          -  Medical contraindication to anesthetic technique (allergy, cardiac condition,
             neurologic condition, localized infection, bleeding disorder).

          -  Patients who are pregnant.
      </textblock>
